{{italic title}} {{Infobox artwork | image_file = Louis Comfort Tiffany - Angel of the Resurrection - Google Art Project.jpg | painting_alignment = | image_size = 200px | title = Angel of the Resurrection | alt = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = [[Tiffany Studios]] | year = 1904 | type = [[Stained glass]] | height_metric = | width_metric = | length_metric = | height_imperial = 168 | width_imperial = 4 | length_imperial = 348 | diameter__metric = | diameter_imperial = | imperial_unit = in | metric_unit = cm | city = [[Indianapolis]] | museum = [[Indianapolis Museum of Art]] | coordinates = | owner = }}
'''''Angel of the Resurrection''''' is a massive [[stained glass]] window by the American [[Art Nouveau]] glass manufacturer [[Tiffany Studios]], now in the collection of the [[Indianapolis Museum of Art]]. It was commissioned by former-[[First Lady of the United States|First Lady]] Mary Lord Harrison as a memorial to her husband, President [[Benjamin Harrison]]. Completed in 1904, the window depicts the [[Michael (archangel)|Archangel Michael]] calling for the dead to rise at the [[Second Coming]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Solga |first=Kim |title=Louis Tiffany Angel of the Resurrection - 1904 |url=http://www.kidsart.com/IS/429.html |publisher=KidsArt |accessdate=27 November 2012 |year=1999 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130312103956/http://www.kidsart.com/IS/429.html |archivedate=12 March 2013 }}</ref>
==Description== Although his trumpet often leads to the assumption that the angel here is [[Gabriel]], he is in fact Michael, using the trumpet to signal the dead to rise again.<ref name=lee>{{cite book|last1=Lee|first1=Ellen Wardwell|last2=Robinson|first2=Anne|title=Indianapolis Museum of Art: Highlights of the Collection|publisher=[[Indianapolis Museum of Art]]|location=[[Indianapolis]]|year=2005|isbn=0936260777}}</ref> Dressed in [[chainmail]] like a crusading knight from the books of [[Sir Walter Scott]], Michael cuts a dashing figure in keeping with the era's romanticism. Although [[Louis Comfort Tiffany|Tiffany]] was absorbed in numerous other projects at the time, he gave his team of gifted designers input before bestowing his approval upon the final composition. Several of his brilliant innovations in glass manufacturing are visible in this piece, including the swirling opalescence of his trademark mottled glass, drapery glass in Michael's robes, and the ruffling on the wings to resemble feathers. The assembly was equally innovative, with lead not merely holding the glass in place but defining the image and creating linear effects. Furthermore, his layering of glass creates dazzling depths and color effects. "Awake Thou That Sleepest. Arise from the Dead and Christ Shall Give Thee Light" from Ephesians 5:14 is inscribed on the window.<ref name=ima/>
==Historical information== ''Angel of the Resurrection'' was commissioned in 1901 for the First Meridian Heights Presbyterian Church in Indianapolis, by Mary Lord Harrison in memory of her husband, President [[Benjamin Harrison]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Glorious Color|url=http://speedwaydailyphoto.blogspot.com/2012/04/glorious-color.html|publisher=Speedway Daily Photo|accessdate=27 November 2012|date=29 April 2012}}</ref> The church had particular importance for Harrison, who had been a church [[Presbyterian polity#Elder|elder]] for over forty years.<ref name=day>{{cite book|last=Day|first=Holliday T.|title=Indianapolis Museum of Art Collections Handbook|year=1988|publisher=[[Indianapolis Museum of Art]]|location=[[Indianapolis]]|isbn=0936260203}}</ref> The total cost, including installation and external glass protection, was $1500.<ref name=harrison/>
===Location history=== The new [[Presbyterian]] church being constructed at the time of Harrison's death housed the window from its dedication in 1905 until it was donated to the IMA in 1972. The original watercolor sketch by Frederick Wilson, a Tiffany designer, resides at the [[Benjamin Harrison Home]].<ref name=harrison>{{cite web|title=The Tiffany Touch|url=http://www.presidentbenjaminharrison.org/learn/exhibits/past-exhibits/19-learn/exhibits/past-exhibits/59-the-tiffany-touch|publisher=[[Benjamin Harrison Home|Benjamin Harrison Presidential Site]]|accessdate=27 November 2012|year=2008}}</ref> ''Angel of the Resurrection'' has the acquisition number 72.75. It is currently on view in the Hunt Rotunda Gallery.<ref name=ima>{{cite web|title=Angel of the Resurrection|url=http://www.imamuseum.org/collections/artwork/angel-resurrection-tiffany-studios-wilson-frederick|publisher=[[Indianapolis Museum of Art]]|accessdate=27 November 2012}}</ref>
