'''''My Drunk Kitchen''''' is a [[cooking show]] and [[comedy]] series of short videos created and posted on [[YouTube]] by [[Hannah Hart|Hannah "Harto" Hart]].<ref name=time_qa>{{cite news|last=Suddath|first=Claire|title=The Pleasures of Cooking While Drunk with Hannah Hart|work=TIME.com|publisher=Time, Inc.|url=http://www.time.com/time/arts/article/0,8599,2079263,00.html|accessdate=June 30, 2011|date=June 22, 2011}}</ref><ref name=hartoandco.com_about>{{cite web|title=Hannah Hart - About - Harto & Co.|url=http://hartoandco.com/about-harto.html|publisher=Harto and Co.|accessdate=July 6, 2011}}</ref> The series features Hart, a [[San Franciscan]] proofreader living in [[Los Angeles]], typically attempting to cook or bake various dishes, or otherwise engaging in some food-related activity, all while imbibing large quantities of alcoholic beverages.<ref name=time_qa /> Most episodes have their own recipe, and occasionally a corresponding beverage. The series has been praised for its drunk humor, [[catchphrase]]s, and the use of [[jump cut]] editing.<ref name=nash_scene>{{cite web|last=Chamberlain|first=Chris|title=My New Chef Crush: My Drunk Kitchen|url=http://www.nashvillescene.com/bites/archives/2011/06/27/my-new-chef-crush-my-drunk-kitchen|work=Nashville Scene|publisher=City Press LLC|accessdate=June 30, 2011}}</ref><ref name=77sq>{{cite web|last=77 Square staff|title=Recent Obsessions: 'The Hunger Games' series, 'My Drunk Kitchen,' and Catherine Deneuve in 'Potiche'|url=http://host.madison.com/entertainment/city_life/article_f1fa317f-a261-5b8c-9361-889e36fd08f8.html|work=77 Square|publisher=madison.com|accessdate=June 30, 2011}}</ref><ref name=cbs_news>{{cite news|last=Johnson|first=Bailey|title="My Drunk Kitchen": I scream, you scream, we all scream for alcohol|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-504784_162-20071682-10391705.html|work=CBS News.com|publisher=CBS Interactive Inc.|accessdate=June 30, 2011}}</ref>

