Towards the end of the second season, Hannah used Indiegogo to raise $25,000 within a month in order to kick-start her roadshow, "Hello, Harto!". She successfully raised $36,000 in four hours and made plans to continue filming "My Drunk Kitchen" on the road. While the roadshow featured Hannah's comedy skits, the show was also used to attract viewers to help volunteer in local food operations.<ref>{{cite web|last=Dunn |first=Gaby |url=http://www.dailydot.com/news/hannah-harto-hart-my-drunk-kitchen-indiegogo/ |title=Hannah Hart crowdfunds "My Drunk Kitchen" tour |publisher=The Daily Dot |date=January 3, 2013 |accessdate=November 23, 2013}}</ref>

After Hannah announced her roadshow, videos were no longer formally organized into seasons.

